{
  "stem": "3631.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Before, the Germans would pick up people from the street to take the labor, and then the Judenrat complained to the gestapo, and we formed the-- the-- the German units had to request people from the-- from the Jewish-- from the ghetto administrator that we need 50 so-and-so, or 20 so-and-so.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they set up-- the commanders, at least, they knew where the people went and when they came back.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "There was the question of food distribution, of administration, and of course of-- of living with the Germans.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this was a difficult part.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I would have hated to be a Juden-- one of the Juden-- one of the Jewish councilmen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It was a great responsibility.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Your life was in danger all the time, because the Germans, if you don't do what-- what they want, that's it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So it-- I think the Jewish Judenrat did as good a job as they could.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was a no win-- no win situation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And of course, if you have a hundred rooms to give out and there are 300 people that want a room, the hundred will be happy, but 200 will be unhappy.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And that-- that was the situation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I was-- I thank God a million times that I was not in-- that I was not in the Judenrat while I worked there in the office and had certain knowledge there.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It-- it-- it was a tough job.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But I think the Jewish-- the Jewish-- the Judenrat people did the best they could, most of them, did the best they could with an impossible-- with an impossible task.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And they did not volunteer to do this.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "They were appointed and said, well, you are this, and you go and say no to a German.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "There is no such thing.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
